  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Tool Steps&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Run a query to identify change requests that need to be Verified (for example: &quot;Resolved Defects&quot;).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select the change request by marking its line on the result set grid. Examine the change.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Perform the required tests to evaluate the resolution. This operation can be done manually or by automation, and&#xD;
        can be performed on a single defect, several defects, or using a full regression test.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Depending on the test result, select the action &lt;strong>Verify_pass&lt;/strong> or &lt;strong>Verify_fail&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Enter information in the mandatory fields. Optionally, enter information in additional optional fields as required&#xD;
        (for example: fail reason).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        If required, add attachment(s) in the &lt;strong>Attachment&lt;/strong> tab.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click &lt;strong>OK&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Hint:&lt;/strong> If you have several defects to verify, you can mark all of those that passed the test and&#xD;
    perform a single Verify_pass operation.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
